

=Bio=

Jukka Peltokoski (born 1974) works as an educational designer and adult educator in KSL Civic Center for Adult Learning which is leftist third sector organization in Finland. Peltokoski has been active in many social movements from environmentalism to precarity issues and basic income initiative. Recently Peltokoski has been founding a new political research platform Commons.fi which is meant to deal widely with commons and p2p issues.

Peltokoski's personal interests lie especially in the questions concerning new cooperativism and commons related social and political struggles.


